'''Piero Martín Hincapié Reyna''' ({{IPA|es|ˈpjeɾo iŋkaˈpje}}; born 9 January 2002) is an Ecuadorian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] or [[left-back]] for [[Premier League]] club [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]], on loan from {{German football updater|BaLeverk}} club [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]], and the [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador national team]].<ref name="SW1">{{cite news|title=Ecuador – P. Hincapié|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/piero-martin-hincapie-reyna/600454/|access-date=31 October 2020|website=Soccerway}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Early career===
Hincapié began playing football at the age of seven, initially for local clubs Escuela Refinería, Emelec and Barcelona.<ref name="LH1">{{cite news|title=El crecimiento futbolístico de quien sueña jugar en Europa|url=https://www.lahora.com.ec/esmeraldas/noticia/1102179972/el-crecimiento-futbolistico-de-quien-suena-jugar-en-europa|accessdate=31 October 2020|work=La Hora|date=21 August 2018|archive-date=25 September 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210925142047/https://lahora.com.ec/esmeraldas/noticia/1102179972/el-crecimiento-futbolistico-de-quien-suena-jugar-en-europa|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name="MAR1">{{cite news|title=Piero Hincapié, el admirador de Puyol que asombra en Ecuador|url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/america/2019/12/11/5df1123b268e3ef80b8b4632.html|accessdate=31 October 2020|work=Marca|date=11 December 2019}}</ref> Aged ten, the defender moved to [[Guayaquil]] with [[C.S. Norte América|Norte América]].<ref name="MAR1"/> After a spell with [[Deportivo Azogues]], he joined [[C.S.D. Independiente del Valle|Independiente del Valle]] in November 2016.<ref name="EU1">{{cite news|title=Piero Hincapié, de Independiente del Valle al primer equipo del Talleres de Córdoba argentino|url=https://www.eluniverso.com/deportes/2020/08/21/nota/7950292/ecuatoriano-piero-hincapie-fichaje-talleres-cordoba-argentina|accessdate=31 October 2020|work=El Universo|date=21 August 2020}}</ref> Hincapié was promoted into their first-team in August 2019 for a [[Ecuadorian Serie A|Serie A]] match with [[Mushuc Runa S.C.|Mushuc Runa]].<ref name="SW1"/> He was selected to start and played the full duration of a narrow home defeat.<ref name="SW1"/> In the subsequent [[2020 Ecuadorian Serie A|2020]] campaign, shortly after winning the [[2020 U-20 Copa Libertadores|U-20 Copa Libertadores]], Hincapié made appearances off the bench against [[C.D. Universidad Católica del Ecuador|Universidad Católica]] and [[C.S.D. Macará|Macará]].<ref name="SW1"/>

===Talleres===
On 20 August 2020, Hincapié agreed a five-year contract with [[Argentine Primera División|Primera División]] side [[Talleres de Córdoba|Talleres]]; who paid [[$]]1,000,000 for 50% of his pass.<ref name="TAL1">{{cite news|title=Piero Hincapié es nuevo refuerzo de Talleres|url=https://www.clubtalleres.com.ar/piero-hincapie-es-nuevo-refuerzo-de-talleres/|accessdate=31 October 2020|work=Talleres|date=20 August 2020}}</ref><ref name="MD1">{{cite news|title=Talleres presentó por Zoom a Piero Hincapié: "Estoy ansioso por jugar"|url=https://mundod.lavoz.com.ar/futbol/talleres-presento-por-zoom-a-piero-hincapie-estoy-ansioso-por-jugar|accessdate=31 October 2020|work=Mundo D|date=1 October 2020}}</ref>

===Bayer Leverkusen===
In August 2021, Hincapié signed for the German [[Bundesliga]] club [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Bayer Leverkusen sign Ecuador teenager Piero Hincapie|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/bayer-leverkusen-sign-ecuador-teenager-piero-hincapie-talleres-16927|access-date=8 October 2021|website=bundesliga.com – the official Bundesliga website|language=en}}</ref> He made his debut on 16 August, coming into the [[UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] group stage match against [[Ferencvárosi TC|Ferencváros]] as Leverkusen won 2–1.<ref>{{Cite web|last=UEFA.com|title=Leverkusen-Ferencváros|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/match/2033182--leverkusen-vs-ferencvaros/|access-date=8 October 2021|website=[[UEFA]]|language=en}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club on 30 September, scoring the opening goal against [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] in a 4–0 victory in the Europa League.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Ruthless Leverkusen punish sloppy Celtic|language=en-GB|work=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58654135|access-date=8 October 2021}}</ref> In the [[2023–24 Bundesliga|2023–24 season]], Hincapié was part of the Leverkusen team that won the club’s first ever Bundesliga title while undefeated the entire league season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://copaamerica.com/en/news/bundesliga-three-south-american-players-were-champions-with-bayer-leverkusen-in-the-bundesliga |title=Bundesliga: Three South American players were champions with Bayer Leverkusen in the Bundesliga |publisher=Copa America |date=15 April 2024 }}</ref>

====Loan to Arsenal====
On 1 September 2025, Hincapié joined [[Premier League]] club [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] on a season-long loan with an option to buy reportedly set at £45&nbsp;million (€52&nbsp;million).<ref>{{cite news |title=Piero Hincapie completes loan move to Arsenal|url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/piero-hincapie-completes-loan-move-arsenal|publisher=Arsenal F.C.|date=1 September 2025|access-date=1 September 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Arsenal sign defender Hincapie from Leverkusen|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/ckglg0x14yko|publisher=BBC Sport|date=1 September 2025|access-date=1 September 2025}}</ref>  He made his debut off the bench against [[Athletic Bilbao]] in the UEFA Champions League on 16 September. He had picked up a groin injury shortly after the game during training.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tbrfootball.com/when-arsenal-actually-expect-piero-hincapie-to-return-from-his-groin-injury/|title=When Arsenal actually expect Piero Hincapie to return from his groin injury|first=Lucas|last=Arnold|date=1 October 2025|website=TBR Football}}</ref> On 26 October, Hincapié made his league debut, also from the bench, against [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]]. He made his full [[EFL Cup]] debut on 29 October against [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]], and full league debut on 23 November against [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Report: Arsenal 2–0 Brighton|url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2025-Oct-29/arsenal-2-0-brighton-hove-albion-match-report|access-date=30 October 2025|date=29 October 2025|last=Peat|first=Charlie|website=Arsenal.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Report: Arsenal 4–1 Tottenham Hotspur|url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2025-Nov-23/arsenal-4-1-tottenham-hotspur-match-report|date=23 November 2025|access-date=29 November 2025|last=James|first=Josh|website=Arsenal.com|language=en}}</ref> Hincapié scored his first goal for Arsenal on 18 February 2026, in a 2–2 draw against [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] at [[Molineux Stadium|Molineux]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Report: Wolverhampton Wanderers 2–2|first=Jonathon|last=Rogers|url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2026-Feb-18/wolves-2-2-arsenal-match-report|website=Arsenal F.C.|date=18 February 2026|access-date=15 March 2026}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Pressure mounts as Arsenal blow two-goal lead to draw at Wolves|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c5ykw23d5v4t|website=BBC Sport|date=18 February 2026|access-date=15 March 2026}}</ref>

On 11 March 2026, Hincapié started for Arsenal against his parent club in the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]], playing the entire 1–1 draw in the first leg of the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Round of 16|Round of 16]] tie at the [[BayArena]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Havertz rescues Arsenal draw at old club Leverkusen|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c5yvwz1d5l2t|date=11 March 2026|access-date=13 March 2026|last=Howell|first=Alex|website=BBC Sport}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Report: Bayer Leverkusen 1–1 Arsenal|url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2026-Mar-11/bayer-leverkusen-1-1-arsenal-match-report|date=11 March 2026|access-date=13 March 2026|last=Rogers|first=Jonathon|website=Arsenal F.C.}}</ref> He then played in the second leg at [[Emirates Stadium]] on 17 March, as Arsenal progressed to the quarter-finals with a 2–0 (3–1 on aggregate) win.<ref>{{cite web|title=Report: Arsenal 2–0 Bayer Leverkusen (3–1)|url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2026-Mar-17/arsenal-2-0-bayer-leverkusen-match-report|first=Josh|last=James|website=Arsenal F.C.|date=17 March 2026|access-date=18 March 2026}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Eze and Rice score as Arsenal cruise into quarters|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c80j473e8rzt|website=BBC Sport|date=17 March 2026|access-date=18 March 2026}}</ref>

Hincapié won the [[2025–26 Premier League|Premier League title]] in his debut season with the club.<ref>{{cite web |last=Austen-Hardy |first=Patrick |url=https://uk.sports.yahoo.com/news/piero-hincapies-hilarious-reaction-bold-030000691.html |title=Piero Hincapie's hilarious reaction after 'bold move' from Arsenal fan Jack Whitehall |publisher=Yahoo! Sports |date=31 May 2026 }}</ref> He later started in the [[2026 UEFA Champions League final|UEFA Champions League final]], where his side lost 4–3 on penalties after a 1–1 draw following extra time.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/live-blogs/psg-vs-arsenal-live-updates-champions-league-final-score-result/tk0jzgMOdrl3/6ixsI83cCwtW/ |title=How PSG beat Arsenal on penalties to win Champions League for second year in a row |publisher=The New York Times |date=31 May 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
Hincapié appeared for the Ecuador U15s in 2017.<ref name="LH1"/> In 2019, Hincapié represented his country as captain at [[Ecuador national under-17 football team|U17]] level.<ref name="SW1"/><ref name="MAR1"/> He played seven times at the [[2019 South American U-17 Championship|South American U-17 Championship]] in Peru, before featuring four times at the subsequent [[2019 FIFA U-17 World Cup|FIFA U-17 World Cup]] in Brazil.<ref name="SW1"/><ref name="MAR1"/>

Hincapié was selected in the 28 player Ecuador squad for the [[2021 Copa América]].<ref>{{cite tweet|author=[[Ecuadorian Football Federation]]|user=LaTri|number=1402825519754797058|title=¡Y los convocados son! Estos son los elegidos por el DT #GustavoAlfaro para encarar un desafío continental: la @CopaAmerica.|date=9 June 2021|access-date=9 June 2021|language=es}}</ref> On 13 June 2021, Hincapié debuted for the [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador senior squad]] in a [[2021 Copa América]] match against Colombia, playing the full match as Ecuador lost 1–0.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Piero Hincapié: Mi debut con la Selección fue una locura. No me imaginaba que iba a salir de inicio, para mí supuso un "shock"|trans-title=Piero Hincapié: My debut with the National Team was crazy. I didn't imagine it was going to start, for me it was "shocking".|url=https://www.eluniverso.com/deportes/ecuatorianos-exterior/piero-hincapie-mi-debut-con-ecuador-fue-una-locura-no-me-imaginaba-que-iba-a-salir-de-inicio-para-mi-supuso-un-shock-nota/|website=El Universo|date=17 February 2022|access-date=18 August 2024|language=es}}</ref>

On 14 November 2022, Hincapié was named in Ecuador's 26-man squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Ecuador, el último en entregar la lista de los 26 jugadores convocados para la Copa del Mundo de Qatar 2022|trans-title=Ecuador, the last to deliver the list of the 26 players summoned for the Qatar World Cup 2022|url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/mundial/nota/_/id/11228629/ecuador-lista-convocados-qatar-2022-mundial-copa-mundo |work=[[ESPN Deportes]]|date=14 November 2022|access-date=14 November 2022|language=es}}</ref> He played 90 minutes in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup Group A|group stage]] win against [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]],<ref>{{Cite news |title=Enner Valencia double gives South Americans win|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63603375|website=[[BBC Sport]]|publisher=[[BBC]]|access-date=29 November 2022}}</ref> the draw against the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]],<ref>{{Cite news |title=Enner Valencia goal earns draw for South Americans|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63672202|website=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|access-date=29 November 2022}}</ref> and defeat against [[Senegal national football team|Senegal]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Ismaila Sarr & Kalidou Koulibaly put Africans into last 16|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63711991|website=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|access-date=29 November 2022}}</ref>

Hincapié was called up to the final 26-man Ecuador squad for the [[2024 Copa América]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eluniverso.com/deportes/futbol/ecuador-presenta-lista-oficial-para-la-copa-america-gonzalo-plata-y-robert-arboleda-quedaron-relegados-nota/|title=Ecuador presenta lista oficial para la Copa América: Gonzalo Plata y Robert Arboleda quedaron relegados|trans-title=Ecuador presents official roster for Copa America: Gonzalo Plata and Robert Arboleda left off the list|publisher=[[El Universo]]|date=29 May 2024|language=es}}</ref>

